() Tj
0 -14 Td
(RECOVERY ACTIONS) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If one stuck record blocks the queue, export the error summary, capture the job ID, and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(clear only the failed record according to the device support workflow.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If the token is stale, sign the user out, reconnect Wi-Fi, and sign back in before rerunning) Tj
0 -14 Td
(sync.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If roaming instability is evident, move to a known-good coverage area and confirm whether) Tj
0 -14 Td
(queued work uploads without restarting the app.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- If the issue follows one device across areas, re-enroll the scanner profile and retest with) Tj
0 -14 Td
(a single sample transaction.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(ESCALATION CRITERIA) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Escalate to network support if multiple scanners in the same zone show reconnect churn or) Tj
0 -14 Td
(low signal history during the same time period.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Escalate to the application support team if multiple devices have healthy connectivity but) Tj
0 -14 Td
(their queues remain blocked by different records.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(- Escalate immediately if clearing the queue risks losing unposted inventory movements and no) Tj
0 -14 Td
(audit export is available.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(FIELD NOTES) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(This guide intentionally distinguishes between a single stuck queue record and a broad outage) Tj
0 -14 Td
(because those produce different evidence. That makes it a stronger corpus document for later) Tj
0 -14 Td
(retrieval than a simple one-size-fits-all checklist.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(A realistic user question might ask whether a scanner should be re-enrolled before or after) Tj
0 -14 Td
(checking whether the problem affects multiple devices. The guide says scope first, then re-) Tj
0 -14 Td
(enroll only if the issue follows one device.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
ET
endstream
